{{md-text text="
#### `channel-header`

The `channel-header` component is used on show, series. and article channel pages. If a given model has a `podcastLinks` attribute, it will render a dropdown menu with links.
"}}
{{code-snippet name="channel-header-normal.hbs"}}
{{!-- BEGIN-SNIPPET channel-header-normal --}}
{{channel-header model=model.channel}}
{{!-- END-SNIPPET --}}

{{md-text text="
The `listenLive` attr should be a `django-page` instance that will render below the producing organization info and schedule line.

For instance, say there's a `listenLive` attribute that looks like this:
"}}
{{code-snippet name="listen-live.js"}}
{{md-text text="You could render a `channel-header` with a listen live button like so:"}}
{{code-snippet name="channel-header-listen-live.hbs"}}
{{!-- BEGIN-SNIPPET channel-header-listen-live --}}
{{channel-header
  model=model.channel
  listenLive=model.listenLive}}
{{!-- END-SNIPPET --}}

{{md-text text="
The `isStaff` attrbute controls whether or not to show a staff link. The `adminURL` should be the `adminRoot` config value plus the `/admin` path prefix.
"}}
{{code-snippet name="channel-header-staff.hbs"}}
{{!-- BEGIN-SNIPPET channel-header-staff --}}
{{channel-header
  model=model.channel
  isStaff=true
  adminURL=adminURL}}
{{!-- END-SNIPPET --}}
